item.title: People talk about "performative males", but I'm a big fan of this new popularity of men reading Bell Hooks.
item.description: https://www.instagram.com/streetlighteyesdontdie It's interesting to me that I believe imgur has more male users than female users, but I bet this post about men's issues will get less engagement than a post about women's issues. Or at least if instead of a guy, it was a hot alt woman quoting Bell Hooks. I think it would be great to discuss men and women's issues here, but we all control the landscape on this planform. While people do often point out I address women's issue more than men's, if I post something and it gets 20 upvotes and no comments, I am just less likely to keep posting that type of content. We build this world together. And yes, I am just less familiar with men's issues, but I am trying to learn.

item.title: Short meme Dump - Memes I shared with my husband #4
item.description:
He absolutely does. To be clear. In fact...he probably deserves a lot more...
Am I annoying the server? Probably yes. Can I stop? Absolutely no.
And they're too expensive to get two!
My childhood unlocked.
My husband used to be a 'sandwich artist' shortly after we first met. For a Canadian chain named Dagwood's.
I just got told I have the start of knee arthritis. I'm 40. So that's neat.
The fit is flex...or whatever kids are saying nowadays. The joke is I'm old and I have no clue what I'm saying when it comes to slang :)
I wonder if I need to mark this post mature...
Hitting 40 with no kids (and the goal to have kids) is a new kind of terror.
I hope this email never finds you. I hope you are free.
Feels like this joke would play well in Scotland.
That's the fun part, I can't!
I'd never have a 'couples' facebook picture as my main one, but I try not to judge on either side of the relationship clingyness spectrum.
I am a chronic complainer and I HATE it. Wanna hear me complain about it?
Flying is the worst. Although I originally typed flaying...which puts things in perspective because I'd rather fly than be flayed or have to flay...
Ohshit. I've always found Superman kind of boring (sorry fans!), but my husband loves him.
But this I can understand.
They hold all the power and they know it.
I'm always so tempted...not by the booze, but the snacks.
Some people are just awesome when you're not feeling well. Hubby is one of those.
Likes tax. By Artist Lonac. They have a lot of great stuff.
